# Document Knowledge Retrieval Agent

## Overview
This project is a **document-based knowledge retrieval system** built using n8n.

It automatically processes uploaded documents and allows users to ask questions based on the content of those documents.

## What This Agent Does
- Monitors cloud storage for new documents
- Processes and indexes document content
- Stores document data in a vector database
- Answers user queries using document context

## Key Features
- Automatic document ingestion
- Context-based question answering
- Scalable document indexing
- Chat-style interaction with stored documents

## Tech Stack
- n8n
- Google Drive
- Vector Database
- OpenAI

## Workflow Steps
1. New document is uploaded to cloud storage
2. Document content is processed and indexed
3. User asks a question related to the document
4. Relevant information is retrieved and returned

## Use Cases
- Internal company knowledge bases
- Document Q&A systems
- Research and report automation

## Notes
- This repository contains an exported **n8n workflow (JSON)**.
- Designed as an internal knowledge automation tool.
